text:
There are 2 carnations for every rose in a bouquet of flowers.

a. If a bouquet has a dozen flowers, what is the ratio of carnations to roses?
b. How many bouquets can be made with 20 roses?
c. How many carnations will be needed to make bouquets with the 20 roses?

After testinf many samples, an electric company determined that approximately 2 of every 1,000 light bulbs on the market are defective. Americans buy approximately 1 billion light bulbs every year. Estimate how many of these bulbs are defective.

Jared and Pedro walk 1 mile in about 15 minutes. they can keep up this pace for several hours.

a. About how far can they walk in 90 minutes?
b. About how far can they walk in 1 hour?
The organizers of an environmental conference order buttons for the participants. They pay $18 for 12 dozen buttons. use what you know about factors and multiples to reason about the ratios.
b. How much do 60 dozen buttons cost?
c. How many dozens of buttons can the organizers buy for $27?
d. How many dozens of buttons can the organizers buy for $63?
Steph makes 10 of his first 15 shots in a basketball free-throw contest. His success rate stays about the same for his next 100 free throws. Use the table to answer the following questions
a. About how many baskets do you expect Steph to make in his next 60 attempts?
b. About how many free throws do you expect him to make in his next 75 attempts?
c. About how many attempts do you expect Steph to take to make 30 free throws?
d. About how many attempts do you expect him to take to make 45 free throws?

Rosco is using a table to plan meals.

a. Complete the table for the macaroni and cheese ingredients.
b. How many ounces of macaroni would you need for 7 cups of cheese?
c. How many cups of cheese would you need for 8- ounces of macaroni?

For ACE 7-9, use Sofia's idea for sharing from Problem 2.3: The distance each team member runs depends on the ratios of their ages. For example, a runner who is twice as old as another runner runs twice as far.
Sofia is 12 years old, and Dembe is 6 years old. If Sofia runs 100 yards, how far does Dembe run? How far do they run altogether?
Jared is 10 years old, and Peter is 15 years old. Together, they run 150 yards. How far does each brother run?
Wynne and Emmett are brother and sister. Wynne runs 180 yards. Emmett runs 120 yards. How old could each of them be?
